{{see|babel}}

==English==

===Etymology===
From the Hebrew [[בבל]] (''Babylon''), from Akkadian ''bāb ili'' (''gate of God''); in [[Genesis]] associated with the idea of confusion.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'beɪbəl/
*:Rhymes: [[rhymes:English:-æbəl|-æbəl]], [[rhymes:English:-eɪbəl|eɪbəl]]

===Noun===
'''Babel'''

# The city and tower in the land of [[Shinar]] where the [[confusion]] of [[language]]s took place, according to the [[Bible]].
#:*Therefore is the name of it called '''Babel'''. - ''Gen. xi. 9.''
# ''Alternative spelling of'' [[babel]].

===Derived terms===
* [[Babel fish]]
* [[tower of Babel]]
* [[Tower of Babel]]

